FBIS4-16651 "drsov075_b_94010" FBIS-SOV-94-075 Daily Report 18 Apr 1994 RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS Political Issues Russia's Choice To Protect CIS Russian Speakers Russia's Choice To Protect CIS Russian Speakers LD1804214294 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 2050 GMT 18 Apr 94 LD1804214294 Moscow ITAR-TASS English BFN [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Aleksandr Kharchenko] [Text] Tver April 19 TASS -- One of the main tasks of the party "Russia's Choice" is to protect Russian-speaking population in former republics of the erstwhile Soviet Union, its leader Yegor Gaydar told ITAR-TASS today. For this purpose "we will use all levers we have, and, in particular, create public opinion aiemd at the protection of the Russian people who are subjected to oppressions by anyone," Gaydar said. Yegor Gaydar eneed his tour of the Tver region today during which he met supporters of the" Russia's Choice" party, representatives of business circles and directors of enteprises of the Upper Volga region.
